The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Atapattu recalled for Tests 

Colombo: Sri Lanka have recalled former captain Maravan Atapattu for their Test series against Bangladesh starting later this month. Atapattu, 36, last played Test cricket against India in 2005, before he was sidelined for 18 months with a serious back injury. 

The right-handed batsman, a veteran of 88 Tests, returns in place of Sanath Jayasuriya, who retired from Test cricket after this years World Cup. 

Uncapped left-hand batsman Malinda Warnapura and left-arm pace bowler Sujeewa de Silva are the two new faces in the 15-man Test squad. 

Muralitharan and Chaminda Vaas will return to Sri Lanka after their county stints for Lancashire and Middlesex respectively, but will miss the ODI series to allow two younger bowlers an opportunity. 

Test squad: Mahela Jayawardene (captain), Upul Tharanga, Maravan Atapattu, Kumar Sangakkara, Chamara Silva, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Prasanna Jayawardene, Chaminda Vaas, Farvez Mahroof, Muttiah Muralidharan, Lasith Malinga, Dilhara Fernando, Malinga Bandara, Malinda Warnapura, Sujeewa de Silva. 

ODI squad: Mahela Jayawardene (capt), Upul Tharanga, Sanath Jayasuriya, Kumar Sangakkara (wk), Chamara Silva, Tillakaratne Dilshan, Jehan Mubarak, Chaminda Vaas, Lasith Malinga, Farvez Mahroof, Upul Chandana, Dilhara Fernando, Chamara Kapugedera, Malinga Bandara, Nuwan Kulasekera. (REUTERS) 




